  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The Architectural Decision document is composed of four parts. The outline of the document is:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;blockquote style=&quot;MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;h4>&#xD;
        1. Architectural Decision&#xD;
    &lt;/h4>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        Describe the Architectural Decision (AD).&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;h4>&#xD;
        2 . Impacts and Implications&#xD;
    &lt;/h4>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        Document any implications of the decision, such as technology choice, cost, and support implications.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;h4>&#xD;
        3. Problem&amp;nbsp;&amp;amp; Constraints&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
    &lt;/h4>&#xD;
    &lt;blockquote style=&quot;MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
        &lt;h5>&#xD;
            3.1 Problem&lt;br />&#xD;
            3.2 Context&lt;br />&#xD;
            3.3 Scope&lt;br />&#xD;
            3.4 Constraints&lt;br />&#xD;
            3.5 Assumptions&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
        &lt;/h5>&#xD;
    &lt;/blockquote>&#xD;
    &lt;h4>&#xD;
        4. Solution Analysis&#xD;
    &lt;/h4>&#xD;
    &lt;blockquote style=&quot;MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
        &lt;h5>&#xD;
            4.1. Solution Architecture&amp;nbsp;&lt;br />&#xD;
            4.2. Solutions Comparative Analysis&amp;nbsp;&lt;br />&#xD;
            4.3. Rationale&#xD;
        &lt;/h5>&#xD;
    &lt;/blockquote>&#xD;
&lt;/blockquote>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Various formats are provided below: Microsoft Word (.dotx and .dot), PDF (.pdf) and Open XML Paper Specification&#xD;
    (.xps).&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
